  "response": "The Insanity workout is an intense, high-intensity interval training (HIIT) program created by fitness trainer Shaun T. Here's a general overview:\n\n1. Equipment needed:\n- Comfortable workout clothes\n- Athletic shoes\n- Water\n- Towel\n- Optional mat\n\n2. Basic workout structure:\n- Warm-up (5-10 minutes)\n- Stretching\n- High-intensity interval exercises\n- Cool-down and stretching\n\n3. Key workout principles:\n- Maximum effort for short intervals\n- Brief recovery periods\n- Bodyweight exercises\n- No equipment required\n- High-intensity cardio and strength training\n\n4. Common exercises include:\n- Jumping jacks\n- High knees\n- Suicide drills\n- Push-up variations\n- Squat jumps\n- Burpees\n\n5. Program details:\n- Typically 60 days long\n- Six days of exercise per week\n- Approximately 40-60 minutes per session\n- Progressively challenging\n\n6. Tips:\n- Stay hydrated\n- Listen to your body\n- Modify exercises if needed\n- Maintain proper form\n- Gradually build intensity\n\nConsult a healthcare professional before starting any intense workout program, especially if you have pre-existing health conditions.",
